description:
The John Hartson Story

Health-Medical Documentary hosted by Steffan Rhodri, published by BBC in 2014 - English narration


Information
------------------------------

A profile of 'Big John' Hartson, one of the best footballers ever to come from Wales. He talks about the night he almost died as he underwent major brain surgery, how he finally sought help for his Ã‚Â£50,000-a-month gambling addiction, and his joy at the birth of a new baby - something he thought would never be possible following his treatment for testicular cancer. He reflects on his remarkable career - his record signing to Arsenal as a teenager - his time as a top premier league goal scorer, his move to Celtic. Now he is in demand as a commentator and pundit on Match of the Day and is a passionate fundraiser. His near death experience drives him to raise awareness of testicular cancer in young men.

